STAGE 1 — Heap Basics

These build the foundation.

1. Complete Binary Tree

Understand:

All levels filled
Last level left to right

Without this, heap makes no sense.

2. Array Representation

Learn formulas:

Left child  = 2i + 1
Right child = 2i + 2
Parent      = (i - 1) / 2

This is how heaps are stored.

3. Min Heap

Rule:

Parent smaller than children

Root contains minimum element.

4. Max Heap

Rule:

Parent greater than children

Root contains maximum element.

STAGE 2 — HEART OF HEAP

MOST IMPORTANT PART.

5. Heapify

Two types:

Heapify Up
Heapify Down

This powers everything.

Without heapify:

insert impossible
delete impossible
heap sort impossible
STAGE 3 — Core Operations
6. Insert

Steps:

Insert at end
Heapify Up

Complexity:

O(logn)

7. Delete

Usually delete root.

Steps:

Replace root with last node
Remove last node
Heapify Down

Complexity:

O(logn)

8. Build Heap

Convert normal array into heap.

Very important interview topic.

Complexity:

O(n)

Interviewers LOVE asking:

Why build heap is O(n) not O(n log n)?
STAGE 4 — Analysis
9. Complexity

Must know:

Operation	Complexity
Insert	O(log n)
Delete	O(log n)
Peek	O(1)
Build Heap	O(n)
Heap Sort	O(n log n)
STAGE 5 — Advanced Concepts
10. Heap Sort

Uses:

Build Heap
Repeated delete

Very common interview algorithm.

Complexity:

O(nlogn)

11. Priority Queue

REAL-WORLD use of heap.

Highest priority item comes first.

Used in:

OS scheduling
Dijkstra algorithm
Task scheduling
12. Kth Largest Element

Classic heap interview problem.

Examples:

kth largest
kth smallest
top k elements

VERY common in coding rounds.

STAGE 6 — Comparison & Theory
13. BST vs Heap

Extremely important theory question.

Main difference:

Heap	BST
Partial ordering	Full ordering
Fast max/min	Fast searching
Complete tree	Not necessarily complete
14. Applications

Know where heaps are used:

Priority Queue
Dijkstra
Heap Sort
Median finding
CPU scheduling
15. Limitations

Interviewers ask this too.

Examples:

Searching is slow
Not fully sorted
Arbitrary deletion difficult